item.description:
🚨 <b>CVE-2026-1527 - Elastic</b><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#eab308;"><b>Média</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#f59e0b;"><b>Elastic</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> NVD<br><b>CVSS:</b> 4.6<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>ImpactWhen an application passes user-controlled input to the upgrade option of client.request(), an attacker can inject CRLF sequences (
) to: * Inject arbitrary HTTP headers * Terminate the HTTP request prematurely and smuggle raw data to non-HTTP services (Redis, Memcached, Elasticsearch) The vulnerability exists because undici writes the upgrade value directly to the socket without validating for invalid header characters: // lib/dispatcher/client-h1.js:1121 if (upgrade) { header += `connection: upgrade
upgrade: ${upgrade}
` }<br><b>Link:</b> https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-1527<br>&nbsp;<br>
